      "I am seriously excited for this. Here's my current query I need to watch changes on:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.table('lists')\r\n  .orderBy({index: 'order'})\r\n  .map(function(list){\r\n    return list.merge({\r\n      steps: r.table('steps').getAll(list('id'), {index:'listId'})\r\n      .orderBy('order')\r\n      .coerceTo('array')\r\n      .map(function(step){\r\n        return step.merge({\r\n          cards: r.table('cards').getAll(step('id'), {index:'stepId'})\r\n          .orderBy('order')\r\n          .coerceTo('array')\r\n        }) \r\n      })\r\n    })\r\n  });\r\n```\r\n\r\nBasically I have three tables. Cards each have a reference to the Step it belong to, and Steps each have a reference to the List it belongs it. These get combined to form a single tree of lists > steps > cards. (Sidenote: If there's a better way to do this query lemme know).\r\n\r\n+1"
